description:
&lt;p&gt;An exciting opportunity has arisen for a qualified GPhC Registered Technician to join our friendly Pharmacy team at Glangwili General Hospital.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are looking for a conscientious individual, who is a team player, has a flexible approach towards the needs of the service, are self-motivated and able to demonstrate professionalism possessing both excellent organisational and communication skills.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Glangwili General Hospital is a busy hospital with approximately 420 beds and provides a range of specialties including Acute Medicine, Critical Care, Surgery, Care of the Elderly, Paediatrics and Women&#39;s Health.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will need to have previous experience of working in an acute hospital ward environment and be motivated, have excellent communication and negotiating skills, working closely with patients .&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You will be required to work under pressure and alone with excellent prioritisation skills. Applicants must be registered as a pharmacy technician with the GPhC and have completed both your ACPT and MMPT accreditation.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Applicants will be required to take part in the week-end and bank holiday rota.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;If the successful applicants&lt;strong&gt; do not&lt;/strong&gt; meet the essential criteria Annex 21 will apply. This will affect the salary as it will be 70% of a Band 5 for the 1st year and 75% of a Band 5 for the 2nd year allowing the successful applicants to gain the necessary accreditations namely MMPT and ACPT.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The ability to speak Welsh is desirable for this post; English and/or Welsh speakers are equally welcome to apply.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interviews will be held on the 24.11.2020&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
